Note that AltHap differs from a previously proposed SCGD algorithm in [32] as follows: (i) AltHap’s novel representation of haplotypes and sequencing reads using binary tensors provides a unified framework for haplotype assembly of diploids as well as biallelic and polyallelic polyploids. The method in [32] is not capable of performing haplotype assembly of polyallelic polyploid genomes. (ii) Unlike [32], AltHap exploits the fact that \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
